{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "I have enough context to outline the change. I\u2019m going to keep the current visual language, but replace the one-off loading/error fragments with a shared feedback layer, connect query failures and connection shifts into a toast store, an...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_29", "text": "I have enough context to outline the change. I\u2019m going to keep the current visual language, but replace the one-off loading/error fragments with a shared feedback layer, connect query failures and connection shifts into a toast store, and wrap the workspace route in an error boundary so unexpected render crashes fail loudly with recovery paths.\n\nPlan:\n1. Inspect the remaining app shell, API, and runtime files that touch fetches or connection state.\n2. Add shared feedback primitives for skeletons, inline spinners, banners, and reusable async state blocks.\n3. Replace local page-specific loading/error markup with the shared components.\n4. Turn the placeholder toast area into a real notification layer and wire it to query/mutation failures plus connection changes.\n5. Add a workspace error boundary with a development-friendly stack trace surface.\n6. Add and update tests for the new feedback behaviors.\n7. Run targeted tests, build/lint, then bring up Docker Compose and do screenshot-backed browser verification before writing the required summary file.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 62, "prompt_index": 29, "prompt_name": "28 \u2014 Error, Loading, and Feedback States", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T03:33:11-07:00"}
