{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Implemented the shared feedback layer for the frontend: reusable banners, skeletons, inline spinners, a real toast store/overlay, backend connection polling with manual refresh, workspace live-feed status messaging, and a dedicated works...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_156", "text": "Implemented the shared feedback layer for the frontend: reusable banners, skeletons, inline spinners, a real toast store/overlay, backend connection polling with manual refresh, workspace live-feed status messaging, and a dedicated workspace error boundary. The changes are centered in [feedback.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/shared/ui/feedback.tsx), [appShellStore.ts](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/state/appShellStore.ts), [AppShell.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/app/AppShell.tsx), [HomePage.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx), [SessionWorkspacePage.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx), and [SessionWorkspaceErrorBoundary.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/SessionWorkspaceErrorBoundary.tsx). I checkpointed the code changes in commit `ccf16b2`.\n\nVerification passed with `cd frontend && npm run test`, `npm run lint`, and `npm run build`. I also captured and reviewed browser screenshots for normal desktop/mobile states and offline/error states under `.artifacts/webapp-qa/`. The required reviewer summary is written at [28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md). One environment gotcha surfaced during offline QA: after intentionally stopping the backend to verify failure states, restarting it exposed a local `secrets.yaml` schema issue unrelated to this frontend work; that limitation is documented in the summary.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 317, "prompt_index": 29, "prompt_name": "28 \u2014 Error, Loading, and Feedback States", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T03:56:53-07:00"}
